The paper focuses on automatic repair of software bugs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of Java language and the Defects4J dataset suggests a programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The experiment involves testing and analyzing the correctness of the generated patches, which relates to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations and challenges of test-suite based repair, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper reports on the computational aspects of the experiment, which could be of interest to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
